<problem id="fs-idm370747456">
<para id="fs-idm374162224"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Which of the following is a possible cause of an unfavorable material quantity variance?</para>
<list id="fs-idm345982688" list-type="enumerated" number-style="upper-alpha">
<item>purchasing substandard material</item>
<item>hiring higher-quality workers</item>
<item>paying more than should have for workers</item>
<item>purchasing too much material</item>
</list>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm362298336">
<para id="fs-idm352110864">A</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm366776368">
<problem id="fs-idm388061424">
<para id="fs-idm368355600"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Which of the following is a possible cause of an unfavorable labor efficiency variance?</para>
<list id="fs-idm380520448" list-type="enumerated" number-style="upper-alpha">
<item>hiring substandard workers</item>
<item>making too many units</item>
<item>buying higher-quality material</item>
<item>paying too much for workers</item>
</list>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm389324288">
<problem id="fs-idm515555744">
<para id="fs-idm385532080"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Which of the following is a possible cause of an unfavorable labor rate variance?</para>
<list id="fs-idm387561024" list-type="enumerated" number-style="upper-alpha">
<item>hiring too many workers</item>
