</section>
<section id="fs-idm480065456" class="questions">
<exercise id="fs-idm374047904">
<problem id="fs-idm635581264">
<para id="fs-idm485553712"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>What causes a favorable variance?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm384878320">
<para id="fs-idm502768112">It is caused by paying or using less than the standard amount.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm364118496">
<problem id="fs-idm332575776">
<para id="fs-idm384496320"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>What causes an unfavorable variance?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm385788816">
<problem id="fs-idm367414736">
<para id="fs-idm364506944"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>When might a favorable variance not be a good outcome?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm378624864">
<para id="fs-idm326677776">It may not be a good outcome when buying substandard material or hiring substandard employees.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm491674432">
<problem id="fs-idm363974112">
<para id="fs-idm368526400"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>When might an unfavorable variance be a good outcome?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm345438960">
<problem id="fs-idm380979776">
<para id="fs-idm370739648"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Identify several causes of a favorable material price variance.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm372768032">
<para id="fs-idm377322976">Causes may include substandard material, quantity discount, negotiated better price, quantity discount, or price drop.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm486443472">
<problem id="fs-idm380526336">
<para id="fs-idm485942624"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Identify several causes of an unfavorable material price variance.</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm384639952">
<problem id="fs-idm520273936">
<para id="fs-idm370237968"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Identify several causes of a favorable material quantity variance.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm378165392">
<para id="fs-idm331476080">Causes may include higher-quality material, better-qualified employees, or a change in manufacturing process.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm357171888">
<problem id="fs-idm374035600">
<para id="fs-idm364933472"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Identify several causes of an unfavorable material quantity.</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm349163952">
<problem id="fs-idm369160608">
<para id="fs-idm365059168"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Identify several causes of a favorable labor rate variance.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm387569728">
<para id="fs-idm334176176">Causes may include less-qualified employees or a change in quality level of employees due to a change in process.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm519538576">
<problem id="fs-idm330039008">
<para id="fs-idm481894032"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Identify several causes of an unfavorable labor rate variance.</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm339832576">
<problem id="fs-idm377904672">
<para id="fs-idm381448368"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Identify several causes of a favorable labor efficiency variance.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm483621168">
<para id="fs-idm350132608">Causes may include better material, higher-quality employees, or a change in process.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm384473200">
<problem id="fs-idm372351456">
<para id="fs-idm356146816"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68073"/>Identify several causes of an unfavorable labor efficiency variance.</para>
